  "prompt": "How do I get rid of a wasp nest in a tree?",
  "response": "Here are some methods to remove a wasp nest in a tree:\n\n1. Professional removal\n- Safest option\n- Pest control experts have proper equipment and protective gear\n\n2. Night-time removal\n- Wasps are less active at night\n- Wear protective clothing\n- Use a long-range wasp spray\n- Spray the nest thoroughly\n- Wait 24 hours to confirm complete elimination\n\n3. Soap and water solution\n- Mix dish soap with water in a spray bottle\n- Spray directly into the nest\n- The soap suffocates the wasps\n\n4. Dust insecticide\n- Use a powder insecticide designed for wasps\n- Apply around nest entrance\n- Wasps will carry it into the nest\n\n5. Natural repellents\n- Peppermint oil\n- Vinegar spray\n- Essential oils\n\nSafety precautions:\n- Wear protective clothing\n- Cover your face and hands\n- Have an escape route\n- Don't attempt removal if allergic to wasp stings\n- Consider professional help for large or hard-to-reach nests\n\nIf unsure or the nest is large, always consult a professional pest control service.",
